<li>There are also considerations of cost. The U.S. spent $6.6 billion in incremental costs on Haiti, the former Yugoslavia, Somalia, and Rwanda from 1992-1995. U.S. General Accounting Office, <I>Peace Operations: U.S. Costs in Support of Haiti, Former Yugoslavia, Somalia, and Rwanda</I>, GAO/NSIAD-96-38, March 1996, p. 2.<P>
